Detailed Description

The section has a list of all the data structures which are exposed to the application.

Typedef Documentation

typedef struct MMWave_AdvancedFrameCfg_t MMWave_AdvancedFrameCfg

Advanced frame configuration.

The structure specifies the configuration which is required to configure the mmWave link to operate in advanced frame mode

typedef struct MMWave_CalibrationCfg_t MMWave_CalibrationCfg

Calibration configuration.

The structure is used to hold the information which is required to setup the calibration of the RF

typedef void(* MMWave_cfgFxn) (MMWave_CtrlCfg *ptrCtrlCfg)

Description
Application registered callback function which is invoked after the configuration has been used to configure the mmWave link and the BSS. This is applicable only for the XWR16xx/XWR18xx/XWR68xx. The BSS can be configured only by the MSS or DSS. The callback API is triggered on the remote execution domain (which did not configure the BSS)

Parameters
[in]ptrCtrlCfgPointer to the control configuration
Return values
Notapplicable
typedef struct MMWave_ChirpCalibrationCfg_t MMWave_ChirpCalibrationCfg

Chirp Calibration configuration.

The structure is used to hold the information which is required to setup the calibration of the RF while operating in the Chirp mode

typedef void(* MMWave_closeFxn) (void)

Description
Application registered callback function which is invoked after the domain has closed the mmWave control module.

Return values
Notapplicable
typedef enum MMWave_ConfigurationMode_e MMWave_ConfigurationMode

Configuration Mode.

The mmWave API can be used in either of the following configuration modes.

typedef struct MMWave_ContCalibrationCfg_t MMWave_ContCalibrationCfg

Continuous Calibration configuration.

The structure is used to hold the information which is required to setup the calibration of the RF while operating in continuous mode

typedef struct MMWave_ContModeCfg_t MMWave_ContModeCfg

Continuous mode configuration.

The structure specifies the configuration which is required to configure the mmWave link to operate in continuous mode

typedef struct MMWave_CooperativeModeCfg_t MMWave_CooperativeModeCfg

mmWave Cooperative mode configuration

The structure is used to describe configuration supported if the mmWave is executing in cooperative mode. In this mode each mmWave module domain is capable of executing the mmWave API and is also responsible for notifying its peer execution domain on the reception of configuration/events.

typedef struct MMWave_CtrlCfg_t MMWave_CtrlCfg

Control configuration.

The structure specifies the configuration which is required to configure and setup the BSS.

typedef enum MMWave_DefaultAsyncEventHandler_e MMWave_DefaultAsyncEventHandler

Default Asynchronous Event Handler.

Enumeration describes the entity which is responsible for the reception of asynchronous events from the BSS. By default the BSS assumes that the MSS is the recepient of asynchronous events such as CPU & ESM Faults etc.

typedef enum MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_e MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode

DFE Data Output Mode.

The enumeration describes the mode in which the DFE outputs the data

typedef enum MMWave_Domain_e MMWave_Domain

Execution Domain.

Enumeration describes the execution domain for the mmWave

typedef enum MMWave_ErrorLevel_e MMWave_ErrorLevel

Error Level.

The mmWave module API can return different error levels. The enumeration describes different error levels. Please refer to the MMWave error decode function on the interpretation of this error level.

See also
MMWave_decodeError
typedef int32_t(* MMWave_eventFxn) (uint16_t msgId, uint16_t sbId, uint16_t sbLen, uint8_t *payload)

Description
Application registered callback function which hooks up with the mmWave Link events generated by the BSS. Please refer to the mmWave Link documentation on more information about these parameters.

NOTE: On the XWR16xx/XWR18xx/XWR68xx (In cooperative mode) asynchronous events are received and passed to the application. The event is also forwarded to the remote domain. In certain cases application would like to reduce the overhead of passing the message to the remote domain in which case the event handler should return 1 which implies that the event is consumed (Hijacked) by the application. Setting the return value to 0 would imply that the event is passed to the remote peer. Applications can use this mechanism to ensure that only certain events are passed between domains.

Parameters
[in]msgIdMessage Identifier
[in]sbIdSubblock identifier
[in]sbLenLength of the subblock
[in]payloadPointer to the payload buffer
Return values
1- Hijack the event and do not pass to the peer domain (If applicable)
0- Pass the event to the peer domain (If applicable)
typedef enum MMWave_ExecutionMode_e MMWave_ExecutionMode

Execution Mode.

The enumeration is valid only for the XWR16xx/XWR18xx/XWR68xx and indicates if the mmWave module is executing in isolation or cooperative mode.

typedef struct MMWave_FrameCfg_t MMWave_FrameCfg

Frame mode configuration.

The structure specifies the configuration which is required to configure the mmWave link to operate in frame mode

typedef struct MMWave_InitCfg_t MMWave_InitCfg

Initial Configuration.

The structure specifies the configuration which is required to initialize and setup the mmWave module.

typedef struct MMWave_LinkCRCCfg_t MMWave_LinkCRCCfg

mmWave Link CRC configuration

The structure is used to describe the CRC configuration. The mmWaveLink messages exchanged between the MSS/DSS and BSS have a checksum applied. The configuration determines if the checksum computation is to use the CRC Driver OR should the computation be done in the software.

typedef struct MMWave_OpenCfg_t MMWave_OpenCfg

Open Configuration.

The structure specifies the configuration which is required to open the MMWave module. Once the MMWave module has been opened the mmWave link to the BSS is operational.

typedef void(* MMWave_openFxn) (MMWave_OpenCfg *ptrOpenCfg)

Description
Application registered callback function which is invoked after the domain has opened the mmWave control module. The BSS has been initialized at this point in time. Applications can use the link API from this point in time. The callback API is only triggered in the remote execution domain.

Parameters
[in]ptrOpenCfgPointer to the open configuration
Return values
Notapplicable
typedef void(* MMWave_startFxn) (MMWave_CalibrationCfg *ptrCalibrationCfg)

Description
Application registered callback function which is invoked on the peer domain just before the mmWave link is started on the BSS.

Parameters
[in]ptrCalibrationCfgPointer to the calibration configuration
Return values
Notapplicable
typedef void(* MMWave_stopFxn) (void)

Description
Application registered callback function which is invoked the mmWave link on BSS has been stopped. This is applicable only for the XWR16xx/XWR18xx/XWR68xx. The BSS can be configured only by the MSS or DSS. The callback API is triggered on the remote execution domain (which did not configure the BSS)

Return values
Notapplicable

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum MMWave_ConfigurationMode_e

Configuration Mode.

The mmWave API can be used in either of the following configuration modes.

Enumerator
MMWave_ConfigurationMode_MINIMAL 

Minimal configuration:

In this mode the mmWave is responsible for the following:-

  • Setting up the mmWave Link Transport to the BSS
  • Start/Stop/Synch capability with the BSS & DSS(if applicable)
  • Asynch BSS Event notification to the peer domain (if applicable)
  • mmWave Link initialization
  • No dynamic memory allocation

The application is responsible for the following:-

  • Using the mmWave Link to configure the BSS
  • Configuration management for the Profile/Chirp and Frame
  • Sending messages to the peer domain (if applicable)

This mode is useful for advanced users.

MMWave_ConfigurationMode_FULL 

Full configuration:

In this mode the mmWave is responsible for the following:-

  • Setting up the mmWave Link Transport to the BSS
  • Start/Stop/Synch capability with the BSS & DSS (if applicable)
  • Asynch BSS Event notification to the peer domain (if applicable)
  • mmWave Link initialization
  • Using the mmWave Link to configure the BSS
  • Configuration management for the Profile/Chirp and Frame
  • Sending messages to the peer domain (if applicable)
  • Dynamic memory allocation

The application is only responsible for tracking mmWave handles.

This mode is useful for basic users.

enum MMWave_DefaultAsyncEventHandler_e

Default Asynchronous Event Handler.

Enumeration describes the entity which is responsible for the reception of asynchronous events from the BSS. By default the BSS assumes that the MSS is the recepient of asynchronous events such as CPU & ESM Faults etc.

Enumerator
MMWave_DefaultAsyncEventHandler_MSS 

The MSS is the default handler for the asynchronous event.

MMWave_DefaultAsyncEventHandler_DSS 

The DSS is the default handler for the asynchronous event.

enum MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_e

DFE Data Output Mode.

The enumeration describes the mode in which the DFE outputs the data

Enumerator
MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_FRAME 

The DFE is operating in Frame mode.

MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_CONTINUOUS 

The DFE is operating in continuous mode.

MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_ADVANCED_FRAME 

The DFE is operating in advanced frame mode.

enum MMWave_Domain_e

Execution Domain.

Enumeration describes the execution domain for the mmWave

Enumerator
MMWave_Domain_MSS 

The mmWave is executing in the MSS domain.

MMWave_Domain_DSS 

The mmWave is executing in the DSS domain.

enum MMWave_ErrorLevel_e

Error Level.

The mmWave module API can return different error levels. The enumeration describes different error levels. Please refer to the MMWave error decode function on the interpretation of this error level.

See also
MMWave_decodeError
Enumerator
MMWave_ErrorLevel_SUCCESS 

The mmWave API was successful. There were no errors detected. There is no reason to perform any error decode here.

MMWave_ErrorLevel_WARNING 

The mmWave API reported a warning. Application can either ignore this error message OR can perform the error decoding to get more information on the actual reason.

MMWave_ErrorLevel_ERROR 

The mmWave API reported an error and applications should perform error decoding to get the exact reason for the failure.

enum MMWave_ExecutionMode_e

Execution Mode.

The enumeration is valid only for the XWR16xx/XWR18xx/XWR68xx and indicates if the mmWave module is executing in isolation or cooperative mode.

Enumerator
MMWave_ExecutionMode_ISOLATION 

Isolation mode: In this mode the mmWave executes only on the DSS or MSS. There is no exchange of the MMWave configuration or events between the DSS or MSS.

MMWave_ExecutionMode_COOPERATIVE 

Cooperative mode: In this mode the mmWave executes on both the DSS and MSS. MMWave configuration and events are shared between the mmWave execution domains.

NOTE: In order for the DSS and MSS realms to communicate with each other the mmWave uses the Mailbox driver with Virtual channel 7. Please ensure that this virtual channel is not used for any other purpose.
